{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876285977,"sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","part":{"id":"prt_d7a799c1c001tJB3qrx6KcjI9I","messageID":"msg_d7a798c2100118fh2nt9lj5RSz","sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6fd678b7af9146d58a3858eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of AgentRuntimeClient for invoking Agent Runtime workloads via Router\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-028.1: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with configuration resolution for router_url, session_id, and timeout parameters.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Initialize with explicit session_id\n21: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`\n22: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n23: - **THEN** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to the provided value and bootstrap SHALL NOT be called\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Initialize without session_id triggers bootstrap\n26: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None`\n27: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n28: - **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL be called and result assigned to `self.session_id`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Router URL from argument\n31: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided as argument\n32: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n33: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to the provided argument\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n36: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n37: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n38: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set from `os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Missing router_url raises ValueError\n41: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is not set\n42: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"router_url must be provided\"\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n46: - **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n47: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n48: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Namespace default\n51: - **GIVEN** `namespace` is not specified\n52: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n53: - **THEN** `self.namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Verbose logging configuration\n56: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is specified\n57: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n58: - **THEN** logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Verbose default is False\n61: - **GIVEN** `verbose` is not specified\n62: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n63: - **THEN** logger level SHALL default to `INFO`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### REQ-028.2: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n68: \n69: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) for automatic resource cleanup.\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Context manager entry\n72: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in `with` statement\n73: - **WHEN** entering the context\n74: - **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n77: - **GIVEN** context block completes without exception\n78: - **WHEN** exiting the context\n79: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Context manager exception exit\n82: - **GIVEN** context block raises an exception\n83: - **WHEN** exiting the context\n84: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` and allow exception to propagate\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### REQ-028.3: AgentRuntimeClient.invoke Method\n89: \n90: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` method for sending JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invoke with payload\n93: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is initialized\n94: - **WHEN** `invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})` is called\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id and payload\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n98: - **GIVEN** `dp_client.invoke()` returns a response object\n99: - **WHEN** `invoke()` completes\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL return `response.json()` (parsed JSON)\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Invoke without session_id raises\n103: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n104: - **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout override\n108: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n109: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n110: - **THEN** timeout `60` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Invoke without timeout uses default\n113: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload)` is called without timeout\n114: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n115: - **THEN** `timeout=None` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()` (uses instance default)\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### REQ-028.4: AgentRuntimeClient.close Method\n120: \n121: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Close calls dp_client.close\n124: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n125: - **WHEN** the method executes\n126: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.dp_client.close()`\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n129: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n130: - **WHEN** the method completes\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeClient closed\"\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### REQ-028.5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Initialization\n136: \n137: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with base URL computation from router_url, namespace, and agent_name.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Base URL computation\n140: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `agent_name=\"test-agent\"`\n141: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n142: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Session constant\n145: - **GIVEN** class is defined\n146: - **WHEN** accessed\n147: - **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: HTTP session creation with pooling\n150: - **GIVEN** client initializes\n151: - **WHEN** `create_session()` is called\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n155: - **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n156: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n157: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### REQ-028.6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id\n162: \n163: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method that GETs the invocation URL and extracts session ID from response header.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Successful session bootstrap\n166: - **GIVEN** Router responds with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n167: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n168: - **THEN** it SHALL return the header value\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Missing session header raises\n171: - **GIVEN** Router response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n172: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Bootstrap sets session header\n176: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` succeeds\n177: - **WHEN** it completes\n178: - **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be set to the bootstrapped value\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Bootstrap makes GET request\n181: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n182: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL be `GET self.base_url` with timeout `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### REQ-028.7: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke\n188: \n189: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` method for POSTing JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Invoke sends POST request\n192: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called with payload\n193: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n194: - **THEN** it SHALL be `POST self.base_url` with JSON body\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Invoke sets session header\n197: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n198: - **WHEN** headers are set\n199: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` SHALL be included\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Invoke sets Content-Type header\n202: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n203: - **WHEN** headers are set\n204: - **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be included\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple default\n207: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called without timeout\n208: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n209: - **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n212: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=60)` is called\n213: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n214: - **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Invoke returns response object\n217: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` completes successfully\n218: - **WHEN** response is received\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Invoke raises on HTTP error\n222: - **GIVEN** Server returns HTTP error status\n223: - **WHEN** `invoke()` receives response\n224: - **THEN** `response.raise_for_status()` SHALL be called (raises `requests.HTTPError`)\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-028.8: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Close calls session.close\n233: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n234: - **WHEN** the method executes\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.session.close()`\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n238: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n239: - **WHEN** the method completes\n240: - **THEN** logger SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient closed\"\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### REQ-028.9: Module Exports\n245: \n246: **Requirement:** The system SHALL export `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in appropriate `__init__.py` files.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n249: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n250: - **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n251: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeClient from root\n254: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n255: - **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n256: - **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Clients subpackage exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n259: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n260: - **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n261: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient from clients\n264: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n265: - **WHEN** `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is executed\n266: - **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### REQ-028.10: Session Header Naming\n271: \n272: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for all SDK Router requests.\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient SESSION_HEADER constant\n275: - **GIVEN** class constant `SESSION_HEADER` is defined\n276: - **WHEN** accessed\n277: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase)\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Bootstrap header extraction\n280: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` reads response header\n281: - **WHEN** extracting header value\n282: - **THEN** it SHALL use lowercase key `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Invoke request header\n285: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` sets request headers\n286: - **WHEN** header dict is constructed\n287: - **THEN** it SHALL use `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` as key (lowercase)\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Data Types\n292: \n293: ```python\n294: # AgentRuntimeClient constructor signature\n295: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n296:     def __init__(\n297:         self,\n298:         agent_name: str,\n299:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n300:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n301:         verbose: bool = False,\n302:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         timeout: int = 120,\n304:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n305:     ) -> None: ...\n306: \n307: # AgentRuntimeClient public methods\n308: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n309:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n310:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n311:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n312:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n313: \n314: # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor signature\n315: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n316:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n317:     \n318:     def __init__(\n319:         self,\n320:         router_url: str,\n321:         namespace: str,\n322:         agent_name: str,\n323:         timeout: int = 120,\n324:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n325:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n326:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n327:     ) -> None: ...\n328: \n329: # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient public methods\n330: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n331:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n332:     def invoke(\n333:         self,\n334:         session_id: str,\n335:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n336:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n337:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n338:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## HTTP Contracts\n344: \n345: ### Agent Runtime Data Plane\n346: \n347: | Operation | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n348: |-----------|--------|-----|---------|------|\n349: | Bootstrap session | GET | `{router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` | (none) | (none) |\n350: | Invoke agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `{\"key\": \"value\", ...}` |\n351: \n352: ### Response Headers\n353: \n354: | Header | Purpose | Required |\n355: |--------|---------|----------|\n356: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Session identifier from bootstrap | Yes (on GET) |\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Error Handling\n361: \n362: | Error | Condition | Exception Type |\n363: |-------|-----------|----------------|\n364: | Missing router_url | Neither argument nor `ROUTER_URL` env var provided | `ValueError` |\n365: | Missing session header | Bootstrap response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` | `ValueError` |\n366: | Invoke without session | `invoke()` called with falsy `session_id` | `ValueError` |\n367: | HTTP error | Server returns 4xx/5xx status | `requests.HTTPError` |\n368: | Network error | Connection refused, timeout, etc. | `requests.RequestException` |\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## Environment Variables\n373: \n374: | Variable | Description | Default |\n375: |----------|-------------|---------|\n376: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router base URL for Agent Runtime | (required) |\n377: | `LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level (if used by get_logger) | INFO |\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Dependencies\n382: \n383: From `pyproject.toml`:\n384: \n385: ```toml\n386: dependencies = [\n387:     \"requests\",              # HTTP client\n388:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",         # JWT token handling\n389:     \"cryptography\",          # Cryptographic operations\n390: ]\n391: \n392: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n393: ```\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ## Acceptance Checklist\n398: \n399: - [ ] `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `AgentRuntimeClient` class implemented\n400: - [ ] `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implemented\n401: - [ ] `agentcube/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`\n402: - [ ] `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `__all__`\n403: - [ ] Router URL resolution from argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n404: - [ ] Session bootstrapping via GET on invocation endpoint\n405: - [ ] Payload invocation via POST with session header\n406: - [ ] Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n407: - [ ] `invoke()` raises `ValueError` without initialized session\n408: - [ ] Bootstrap raises `ValueError` if header missing\n409: - [ ] Timeout defaults: 120s read / 5.0s connect\n410: - [ ] Per-call timeout override support\n411: - [ ] HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n412: - [ ] Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header usage\n413: - [ ] Unit tests for session bootstrapping\n414: - [ ] Unit tests for invoke with/without timeout\n415: - [ ] Unit tests for context manager cleanup\n416: - [ ] Unit tests for error cases\n417: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for AgentRuntimeClient\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ## Open Questions\n422: \n423: 1. Should `invoke()` expose additional response metadata beyond parsed JSON (e.g., status code, headers)?\n424: 2. Should retry logic be added for transient HTTP failures?\n425: 3. Should streaming response support be added for long-running agent operations?\n426: 4. Should agent runtime discovery (list available agents) be supported?\n\n(End of file - total 426 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of AgentRuntimeClient for invoking Agent Runtime workloads via Router\n\n**Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-028.1: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with configuration resolution for router_url, session_id, and timeout parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with explicit session_id","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876285946,"end":1775876285975}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876285982,"sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","part":{"id":"prt_d7a79a126001ZhpZUq2afoTm06","messageID":"msg_d7a798c2100118fh2nt9lj5RSz","sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ff11898431ea4c1990adda1f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n4: \n5: ## Architecture\n6: \n7: ### Overview\n8: \n9: The AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    Public API Layer                          │\n14: │  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n15: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n16:                               │\n17:         ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n18:         │                                           │\n19:         ▼                                           ▼\n20: ┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐\n21: │   Control Plane   │                   │     Data Plane        │\n22: │  ControlPlane     │                   │  CodeInterpreter      │\n23: │     Client        │                   │  DataPlaneClient      │\n24: │                   │                   │                       │\n25: │  (Session Mgmt)   │                   │  (Code/File Ops)      │\n26: └───────────────────┘                   └───────────────────────┘\n27:                                                  │\n28:                               ┌──────────────────┴──────────────┐\n29:                               │                                 │\n30:                               ▼                                 ▼\n31:                     ┌───────────────────┐           ┌───────────────────┐\n32:                     │   AgentRuntime    │           │    HTTP Client    │\n33:                     │  DataPlaneClient  │           │   Utilities       │\n34:                     │                   │           │                   │\n35:                     │  (Agent Invoke)   │           │  (Session, Auth)  │\n36:                     └───────────────────┘           └───────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Component Responsibilities\n40: \n41: | Component | Responsibility |\n42: |-----------|---------------|\n43: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | High-level facade for code interpretation; orchestrates control plane session lifecycle and data plane operations |\n44: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level facade for agent runtime invocations; manages session bootstrapping and payload delivery |\n45: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client; session creation/deletion via Workload Manager |\n46: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; code execution and file operations via Router |\n47: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; agent invocation via Router |\n48: | `create_session` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n49: | `read_token_from_file` | Service account token loading utility |\n50: | `get_logger` | Structured logging configuration |\n51: \n52: ### Design Patterns\n53: \n54: 1. **Facade Pattern**: `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` provide simplified interfaces to complex subsystems\n55: 2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both high-level clients support `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n56: 3. **Dependency Injection**: Lower-level clients are instantiated by higher-level clients with resolved configuration\n57: 4. **Environment Configuration**: Settings resolve from constructor args → environment variables → defaults\n58: \n59: ## Data Structures\n60: \n61: ### Class Instance Attributes\n62: \n63: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n64: \n65: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n66: |-----------|------|-------------|\n67: | `name` | `str` | Interpreter session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n68: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n69: | `ttl` | `int` | Session time-to-live in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n70: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n71: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n72: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane client instance |\n73: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n74: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (provided or created) |\n75: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n76: \n77: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n78: \n79: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n80: |-----------|------|-------------|\n81: | `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name |\n82: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n83: | `timeout` | `int` | Default request timeout in seconds (default: `120`) |\n84: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`) |\n85: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n86: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n87: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (bootstrapped or provided) |\n88: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n89: \n90: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n91: \n92: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n93: |-----------|------|-------------|\n94: | `base_url` | `str` | Workload Manager API base URL |\n95: | `auth_token` | `str` | Bearer token for authentication |\n96: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n97: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n98: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n99: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n100: \n101: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n102: \n103: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n104: |-----------|------|-------------|\n105: | `session_id` | `str` | Session identifier for header |\n106: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n107: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n108: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n109: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n110: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n111: \n112: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n113: \n114: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n115: |-----------|------|-------------|\n116: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n117: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n118: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n119: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n120: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n121: \n122: ### Exception Classes\n123: \n124: ```\n125: AgentCubeError (base)\n126: ├── CommandExecutionError\n127: │   ├── exit_code: int\n128: │   ├── stderr: str\n129: │   └── command: Optional[str]\n130: ├── SessionError\n131: └── DataPlaneError\n132: ```\n133: \n134: | Exception | Raised When |\n135: |-----------|-------------|\n136: | `AgentCubeError` | Base class; not raised directly |\n137: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n138: | `SessionError` | Reserved for session creation/management failures |\n139: | `DataPlaneError` | Reserved for data plane operation failures |\n140: \n141: ### Request/Response DTOs\n142: \n143: #### Control Plane - Create Session Request\n144: \n145: ```json\n146: {\n147:   \"name\": \"string\",\n148:   \"namespace\": \"string\",\n149:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n150:   \"metadata\": {}\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### Control Plane - Create Session Response\n155: \n156: ```json\n157: {\n158:   \"sessionId\": \"string\"\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Request\n163: \n164: ```json\n165: {\n166:   \"command\": [\"string\"] | \"string\",\n167:   \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Response\n172: \n173: ```json\n174: {\n175:   \"stdout\": \"string\",\n176:   \"stderr\": \"string\",\n177:   \"exit_code\": 0\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: #### Data Plane - Write File Request\n182: \n183: ```json\n184: {\n185:   \"path\": \"string\",\n186:   \"content\": \"base64-encoded-string\",\n187:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n188: }\n189: ```\n190: \n191: #### Data Plane - List Files Response\n192: \n193: ```json\n194: {\n195:   \"files\": [\"string\"]\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ## API Contracts\n200: \n201: ### Control Plane API (Workload Manager)\n202: \n203: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n204: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n205: | Create Session | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `CreateSessionRequest` | `sessionId: str` |\n206: | Delete Session | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | - | `bool` |\n207: \n208: #### Create Session\n209: \n210: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n211: - **Method**: `POST`\n212: - **Headers**:\n213:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n214:   - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present)\n215: - **Body**:\n216:   ```json\n217:   {\n218:     \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n219:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n220:     \"ttl\": 3600,\n221:     \"metadata\": {}\n222:   }\n223:   ```\n224: - **Success Response** (200/201):\n225:   ```json\n226:   {\n227:     \"sessionId\": \"ci-abc123\"\n228:   }\n229:   ```\n230: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n231: \n232: #### Delete Session\n233: \n234: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n235: - **Method**: `DELETE`\n236: - **Headers**: Same as Create Session\n237: - **Success Response** (200/204): `True`\n238: - **Not Found** (404): `True` (treated as idempotent success)\n239: - **Other Errors**: Log and return `False`\n240: \n241: ### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter via Router)\n242: \n243: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n244: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n245: | Execute Command | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n246: | Run Code | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n247: | Write File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | `WriteFileRequest` (JSON) | `None` |\n248: | Upload File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | Multipart form | `None` |\n249: | Download File | GET | `{base_url}api/files/{path}` | - | `bytes` |\n250: | List Files | GET | `{base_url}api/files` | Query: `path` | `List[str]` |\n251: \n252: #### Execute Command\n253: \n254: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/execute`\n255: - **Method**: `POST`\n256: - **Headers**:\n257:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n258:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n259: - **Body**:\n260:   ```json\n261:   {\n262:     \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n263:     \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n264:   }\n265:   ```\n266: - **Success Response** (200): stdout string\n267: - **Error Response**: Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n268: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` for read side\n269: \n270: #### Write File\n271: \n272: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n273: - **Method**: `POST`\n274: - **Headers**:\n275:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n276:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n277: - **Body**:\n278:   ```json\n279:   {\n280:     \"path\": \"/app/test.py\",\n281:     \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\",\n282:     \"mode\": \"0644\"\n283:   }\n284:   ```\n285: \n286: #### Upload File (Multipart)\n287: \n288: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n289: - **Method**: `POST`\n290: - **Headers**:\n291:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n292: - **Form Data**:\n293:   - `file`: binary file content\n294:   - `path`: remote file path\n295:   - `mode`: file mode (default: `\"0644\"`)\n296: \n297: #### Download File\n298: \n299: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n300: - **Method**: `GET`\n301: - **Headers**:\n302:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n303: - **Query Params**: `stream=True`\n304: - **Response**: Binary file content\n305: \n306: #### List Files\n307: \n308: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n309: - **Method**: `GET`\n310: - **Headers**:\n311:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n312: - **Query Params**: `path` (default: `\".\"`)\n313: - **Response**: JSON array of file paths\n314: \n315: ### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime via Router)\n316: \n317: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n318: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n319: | Bootstrap Session | GET | `{base_url}` | - | `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n320: | Invoke Agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `requests.Response` |\n321: \n322: #### Bootstrap Session ID\n323: \n324: - **URL**: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n325: - **Method**: `GET`\n326: - **Headers**: None (session default only)\n327: - **Success Response**: Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n328: - **Error**: Raises `ValueError` if header missing\n329: \n330: #### Invoke Agent\n331: \n332: - **URL**: `{base_url}`\n333: - **Method**: `POST`\n334: - **Headers**:\n335:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n337: - **Body**: JSON payload dict\n338: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n339: \n340: ## Error Handling\n341: \n342: ### Exception Hierarchy\n343: \n344: ```python\n345: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n346:     \"\"\"Base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors\"\"\"\n347:     pass\n348: \n349: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n350:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails\"\"\"\n351:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n352:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n353:         self.stderr = stderr\n354:         self.command = command\n355:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n356: \n357: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n358:     \"\"\"Reserved for session creation/management failures\"\"\"\n359:     pass\n360: \n361: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n362:     \"\"\"Reserved for data plane operation failures\"\"\"\n363:     pass\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ### Error Handling Strategy\n367: \n368: | Component | Error Source | Handling Strategy |\n369: |-----------|--------------|-------------------|\n370: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `_init_data_plane()` failure | Log warning, delete session, re-raise |\n371: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | Context manager exit | Call `stop()` for cleanup regardless of exception |\n372: | `execute_command` | Non-zero exit code | Raise `CommandExecutionError` |\n373: | `ControlPlaneClient` | 404 on delete | Return `True` (idempotent) |\n374: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Other HTTP errors | Log and return `False` |\n375: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Missing session header | Raise `ValueError` |\n376: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError` |\n377: | HTTP clients | `requests.RequestException` | Propagate to caller |\n378: \n379: ### Cleanup Guarantees\n380: \n381: 1. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` implement `__enter__` and `__exit__` for deterministic cleanup\n382: 2. **Stop Method**: `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` ensures:\n383:    - Data plane session closure\n384:    - Control plane session deletion (if created internally)\n385:    - HTTP session close\n386: 3. **Close Method**: `AgentRuntimeClient.close()` ensures HTTP session closure\n387: 4. **Exception Safety**: Cleanup occurs regardless of exception type in `__exit__`\n388: \n389: ## Testing Strategy\n390: \n391: ### Test Categories\n392: \n393: | Category | Scope | Tools | Location |\n394: |----------|-------|-------|----------|\n395: | Unit Tests | Individual classes/methods | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` | `tests/unit/` |\n396: | Integration Tests | Client-server interaction | `pytest`, test fixtures | `tests/integration/` |\n397: | End-to-End Tests | Full workflow validation | `pytest`, live environment | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n398: \n399: ### Unit Test Strategy\n400: \n401: #### Mocking Approach\n402: \n403: ```python\n404: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n405: import pytest\n406: \n407: # Example: Mock HTTP session\n408: @pytest.fixture\n409: def mock_session():\n410:     session = Mock(spec=requests.Session)\n411:     session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n412:     return session\n413: \n414: # Example: Patch create_session\n415: @patch('agentcube.utils.http.create_session')\n416: def test_control_plane_create_session(mock_create_session):\n417:     mock_session = Mock()\n418:     mock_session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n419:     mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n420:     \n421:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://test\")\n422:     session_id = client.create_session()\n423:     \n424:     assert session_id == \"test-123\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: #### Test Coverage Targets\n428: \n429: | Module | Coverage Target | Key Scenarios |\n430: |--------|-----------------|---------------|\n431: | `code_interpreter.py` | 90% | Context manager, session lifecycle, delegation |\n432: | `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager |\n433: | `control_plane.py` | 95% | HTTP request construction, error handling |\n434: | `code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL construction, timeout logic, file operations |\n435: | `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | Session bootstrap, invoke |\n436: | `utils/` | 100% | Session creation, token reading, logging |\n437: | `exceptions.py` | 100% | Exception initialization |\n438: \n439: ### Integration Test Strategy\n440: \n441: #### Test Fixtures\n442: \n443: ```python\n444: @pytest.fixture\n445: def code_interpreter_client():\n446:     client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n447:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n448:         workload_manager_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n449:         namespace=\"test\"\n450:     )\n451:     yield client\n452:     client.stop()\n453: \n454: @pytest.fixture\n455: def agent_runtime_client():\n456:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n457:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n458:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n459:         namespace=\"test\"\n460:     )\n461:     yield client\n462:     client.close()\n463: ```\n464: \n465: #### Integration Test Scenarios\n466: \n467: | Test | Steps | Expected Outcome |\n468: |------|-------|------------------|\n469: | `test_code_execution` | Create session → Execute `print(\"hello\")` | stdout contains \"hello\" |\n470: | `test_file_operations` | Write file → List files → Download file | File exists, content matches |\n471: | `test_agent_invoke` | Bootstrap session → Invoke agent | Valid response from agent |\n472: \n473: ### End-to-End Test\n474: \n475: Located at `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`:\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n479: \"\"\"End-to-end test for Code Interpreter with PicoD\"\"\"\n480: \n481: import sys\n482: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n483: \n484: def main():\n485:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n486:         router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n487:         namespace=\"default\"\n488:     ) as client:\n489:         # Test 1: Simple command\n490:         result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'hello'\")\n491:         assert \"hello\" in result\n492:         \n493:         # Test 2: Python code\n494:         result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(2 + 2)\")\n495:         assert \"4\" in result\n496:         \n497:         # Test 3: File write and read\n498:         client.write_file(\"test content\", \"/app/test.txt\")\n499:         result = client.execute_command(\"cat /app/test.txt\")\n500:         assert \"test content\" in result\n501:         \n502:     print(\"All E2E tests passed!\")\n503:     return 0\n504: \n505: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n506:     sys.exit(main())\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ### Continuous Integration\n510: \n511: | Pipeline Stage | Tests | Environment |\n512: |----------------|-------|-------------|\n513: | Lint | `pytest --flake8`, `mypy` | Isolated |\n514: | Unit Test | `pytest tests/unit/` | Isolated |\n515: | Integration Test | `pytest tests/integration/` | Test cluster |\n516: | E2E Test | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | Staging environment |\n517: \n518: ## Dependencies\n519: \n520: ### Runtime Dependencies\n521: \n522: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n523: |---------|---------|---------|\n524: | `requests` | `>=2.28.0` | HTTP client |\n525: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling |\n526: | `cryptography` | `>=38.0.0` | Cryptographic operations |\n527: \n528: ### Build Configuration\n529: \n530: ```toml\n531: [build-system]\n532: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n533: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n534: \n535: [project]\n536: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n537: version = \"0.1.0\"\n538: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n539: dependencies = [\n540:     \"requests\",\n541:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n542:     \"cryptography\",\n543: ]\n544: \n545: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n546: where = [\".\"]\n547: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n548: namespaces = false\n549: ```\n550: \n551: ### Development Dependencies\n552: \n553: | Package | Purpose |\n554: |---------|---------|\n555: | `pytest` | Test framework |\n556: | `pytest-mock` | Mocking utilities |\n557: | `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting |\n558: | `mypy` | Static type checking |\n559: | `flake8` | Code style linting |\n560: | `black` | Code formatting |\n561: \n562: ## Logging Strategy\n563: \n564: ### Logger Configuration\n565: \n566: ```python\n567: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n568:     logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n569:     logger.setLevel(level)\n570:     \n571:     if not logger.handlers:\n572:         handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n573:         formatter = logging.Formatter(\n574:             '%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s'\n575:         )\n576:         handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n577:         logger.addHandler(handler)\n578:     \n579:     return logger\n580: ```\n581: \n582: ### Log Levels\n583: \n584: | Level | Usage |\n585: |-------|-------|\n586: | `DEBUG` | HTTP request/response details, configuration resolution |\n587: | `INFO` | Session creation/deletion, major lifecycle events |\n588: | `WARNING` | Non-critical errors (404 on delete), fallback behavior |\n589: | `ERROR` | Operation failures, exceptions |\n590: \n591: ### Example Log Output\n592: \n593: ```\n594: 2024-01-15 10:30:00 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Creating session: my-interpreter\n595: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.control_plane - DEBUG - POST http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter\n596: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Session created: ci-abc123\n597: 2024-01-15 10:30:02 - agentcube.data_plane - DEBUG - POST http://router:8080/.../api/execute\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ## Security Considerations\n601: \n602: ### Authentication\n603: \n604: 1. **Control Plane**: Bearer token via `Authorization` header\n605:    - Token from constructor argument `auth_token`\n606:    - Fallback to service account token file: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n607: \n608: 2. **Data Plane**: JWT handled by Router; SDK does not set `Authorization` header\n609: \n610: ### Session ID Security\n611: \n612: - Session ID transmitted in `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n613: - Session ID should be treated as sensitive (grants access to sandbox)\n614: - Automatic session cleanup on context manager exit\n615: \n616: ### File Operations\n617: \n618: - No local file system access outside provided paths\n619: - Upload/download operations require explicit local path specification\n620: - Remote file paths validated/cleaned before use\n\n(End of file - total 620 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public API Layer                          │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n        ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n        │                                           │\n        ▼                                           ▼\n┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775876285953,"end":1775876285978}}}}
