{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876397653,"sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","part":{"id":"prt_d7a79cce4001X820zNgpDyjqNo","messageID":"msg_d7a79a676001lOu0iLI4hT8GnT","sessionID":"ses_285869f5effet5N5xG17euf83f","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_30b4325e8c664d70817a7d9c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md","content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `AgentRuntimeClient` feature in the AgentCube Python SDK.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│       AgentRuntimeClient                │\n│  (High-level Facade)                    │\n│  - agent_name                           │\n│  - namespace                            │\n│  - session_id (bootstrapped or given)   │\n│  - dp_client                            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    │\n                    │ delegates to\n                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│   AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient           │\n│  (HTTP Client for Router)               │\n│  - base_url                             │\n│  - session (requests.Session)           │\n│  - timeout / connect_timeout            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n1. **Facade Pattern**: `AgentRuntimeClient` provides simplified interface hiding data plane complexity\n2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Supports `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n3. **Environment Configuration**: Router URL resolves from argument → `ROUTER_URL` env var → error\n4. **Session Bootstrap**: Auto-retrieves session ID from Router if not provided\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### `AgentRuntimeClient` Instance Attributes\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n|-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name | (required) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | `\"default\"` |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | from `ROUTER_URL` env |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging | `False` |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier | bootstrapped or given |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client | - |\n\n### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` Instance Attributes\n\n| Attribute | Type | Description | Default |\n|-----------|------|-------------|---------|\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL | (required) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace | (required) |\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name | (required) |\n| `base_url` | `str` | Computed invocation URL | - |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (seconds) | `120` |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (seconds) | `5.0` |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with pooling | - |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger | - |\n\n### Class Constants\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"  # Lowercase header name\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Public Interface\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ) -> None\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Public Interface\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### HTTP Contracts\n\n#### Bootstrap Session (GET)\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Method** | `GET` |\n| **URL** | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` |\n| **Headers** | (session defaults only) |\n| **Body** | (none) |\n| **Success Response** | 200 with header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` |\n| **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` |\n\n#### Invoke Agent (POST)\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Method** | `POST` |\n| **URL** | `{base_url}` (computed in init) |\n| **Headers** | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` |\n| **Body** | JSON payload dict |\n| **Success Response** | 200 OK, response body parsed as JSON |\n| **Timeout** | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n\n### Base URL Computation\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Matrix\n\n| Error Condition | Exception Type | Message |\n|-----------------|----------------|---------|\n| Missing `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` env var | `ValueError` | Contains \"router_url must be provided\" |\n| Bootstrap response lacks session header | `ValueError` | `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n| `invoke()` called without initialized session | `ValueError` | `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"` |\n| HTTP error (4xx/5xx) | `requests.HTTPError` | Raised by `response.raise_for_status()` |\n| Network error | `requests.RequestException` | Propagated to caller |\n\n### Error Handling Flow\n\n```\nAgentRuntimeClient.__init__\n    ├─ Router URL missing → raise ValueError\n    └─ session_id is None\n        └─ bootstrap_session_id()\n            ├─ GET request fails → raise requests.RequestException\n            └─ Missing header → raise ValueError\n\nAgentRuntimeClient.invoke\n    ├─ session_id is None → raise ValueError\n    └─ dp_client.invoke()\n        ├─ HTTP error → raise requests.HTTPError\n        └─ Network error → raise requests.RequestException\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Test File: `tests/unit/test_agent_runtime.py`\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClientInit:\n    def test_init_with_explicit_session_id(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is provided\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN bootstrap is NOT called\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id') as mock_bootstrap:\n            client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n                agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n                router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n                session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n            )\n            assert client.session_id == \"test-session-123\"\n            mock_bootstrap.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_init_without_session_id_triggers_bootstrap(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN bootstrap IS called\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, 'bootstrap_session_id', \n                          return_value=\"bootstrapped-session\"):\n            client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n                agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n                router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n            )\n            assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-session\"\n\n    def test_router_url_from_env(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN router_url not provided but ROUTER_URL env var set\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN router_url from env\"\"\"\n        with patch('os.getenv', return_value=\"http://from-env:8080\"):\n            client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n                agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n                router_url=None\n            )\n            assert client.router_url == \"http://from-env:8080\"\n\n    def test_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN neither router_url nor ROUTER_URL env var\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n            with patch('os.getenv', return_value=None):\n                AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\")\n\n    def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        assert client.timeout == 120\n        assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n\n    def test_namespace_default(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN namespace not specified\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN defaults to 'default'\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClientContextManager:\n    def test_context_manager_enter(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN with statement used\n           WHEN entering context\n           THEN returns self\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        with client as c:\n            assert c is client\n\n    def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN context block exits\n           WHEN __exit__ called\n           THEN close() is called\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        client.close = Mock()\n        with client:\n            pass\n        client.close.assert_called_once()\n\n    def test_context_manager_exit_with_exception(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN context block raises exception\n           WHEN __exit__ called\n           THEN close() still called\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        client.close = Mock()\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n            with client:\n                raise ValueError(\"test error\")\n        client.close.assert_called_once()\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClientInvoke:\n    def test_invoke_with_payload(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN session_id initialized\n           WHEN invoke called with payload\n           THEN dp_client.invoke called\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"test-session\"\n        )\n        client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {\"result\": \"ok\"}))\n        result = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n        client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n            session_id=\"test-session\",\n            payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n            timeout=None\n        )\n        assert result == {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n\n    def test_invoke_returns_parsed_json(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN dp_client.invoke returns response\n           WHEN invoke completes\n           THEN parsed JSON returned\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"test-session\"\n        )\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n        client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        result = client.invoke({\"test\": \"payload\"})\n        assert result == {\"status\": \"success\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n\n    def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN session_id is None\n           WHEN invoke called\n           THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=None\n        )\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"):\n            client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n\n    def test_invoke_with_timeout_override(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n           WHEN request sent\n           THEN timeout=60 passed to dp_client\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"test-session\"\n        )\n        client.dp_client.invoke = Mock(return_value=Mock(json=lambda: {}))\n        client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=60)\n        client.dp_client.invoke.assert_called_once_with(\n            session_id=\"test-session\",\n            payload={\"message\": \"hello\"},\n            timeout=60\n        )\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClientClose:\n    def test_close_calls_dp_client_close(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n           WHEN method executes\n           THEN dp_client.close() called\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        client.dp_client.close = Mock()\n        client.close()\n        client.dp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInit:\n    def test_base_url_computation(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN router_url, namespace, agent_name provided\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN base_url computed correctly\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        expected = \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n        assert client.base_url == expected\n\n    def test_session_header_constant(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN class constant accessed\n           WHEN SESSION_HEADER read\n           THEN equals lowercase header name\"\"\"\n        assert AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER == \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def test_timeout_defaults(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN timeout/connect_timeout not specified\n           WHEN client initializes\n           THEN defaults applied\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        assert client.timeout == 120\n        assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientBootstrap:\n    def test_successful_bootstrap(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN Router responds with session header\n           WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n           THEN header value returned\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"bootstrapped-session-123\"}\n        client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        result = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n        assert result == \"bootstrapped-session-123\"\n\n    def test_missing_header_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN Response lacks session header\n           WHEN bootstrap_session_id called\n           THEN ValueError raised\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.headers = {}\n        client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n            client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n    def test_bootstrap_makes_get_request(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN bootstrap_session_id called\n           WHEN request sent\n           THEN GET to base_url with timeout tuple\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n        client.session.get = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        client.bootstrap_session_id()\n        client.session.get.assert_called_once_with(\n            client.base_url,\n            timeout=(client.connect_timeout, client.timeout)\n        )\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInvoke:\n    def test_invoke_sends_post_request(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with payload\n           WHEN request sent\n           THEN POST to base_url with JSON body\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        payload = {\"message\": \"hello\", \"data\": [1, 2, 3]}\n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload=payload)\n        \n        client.session.post.assert_called_once()\n        call_args = client.session.post.call_args\n        assert call_args[0][0] == client.base_url\n        assert call_args[1]['json'] == payload\n\n    def test_invoke_sets_session_header(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n           WHEN headers constructed\n           THEN x-agentcube-session-id included\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n        \n        headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n        assert headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] == \"test-session\"\n\n    def test_invoke_sets_content_type_header(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called\n           WHEN headers constructed\n           THEN Content-Type: application/json included\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n        \n        headers = client.session.post.call_args[1]['headers']\n        assert headers[\"Content-Type\"] == \"application/json\"\n\n    def test_invoke_timeout_default(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called without timeout\n           WHEN request sent\n           THEN timeout tuple with instance default used\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            timeout=120,\n            connect_timeout=5.0\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n        \n        timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n        assert timeout == (5.0, 120)\n\n    def test_invoke_timeout_override(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke called with timeout=60\n           WHEN request sent\n           THEN timeout tuple uses override\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60)\n        \n        timeout = client.session.post.call_args[1]['timeout']\n        assert timeout == (client.connect_timeout, 60)\n\n    def test_invoke_returns_response(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN invoke completes successfully\n           WHEN response received\n           THEN requests.Response object returned\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = \"test-session\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        client.session.post = Mock(return_value=mock_response)\n        \n        result = client.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={\"test\": \"data\"})\n        \n        assert result is mock_response\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientClose:\n    def test_close_calls_session_close(self):\n        \"\"\"GIVEN close() called\n           WHEN method executes\n           THEN session.close() called\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        client.session.close = Mock()\n        client.close()\n        client.session.close.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Module | Target | Key Scenarios |\n|--------|--------|---------------|\n| `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager, error cases |\n| `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL computation, bootstrap, invoke, session header |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef agent_runtime_client():\n    \"\"\"Integration test fixture for AgentRuntimeClient\"\"\"\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\", \"http://localhost:8080\"),\n        namespace=\"test\"\n    )\n    yield client\n    client.close()\n\ndef test_agent_invoke_integration(agent_runtime_client):\n    \"\"\"Test agent invocation against live Router\"\"\"\n    response = agent_runtime_client.invoke({\n        \"action\": \"test\",\n        \"payload\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n    })\n    assert response is not None\n```\n\n## Module Exports\n\n### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` with `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` with `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Implement router URL resolution (arg → `ROUTER_URL` env → error)\n- [ ] Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n- [ ] Implement payload invocation via POST with session header\n- [ ] Implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n- [ ] Implement timeout defaults (120s read / 5.0s connect)\n- [ ] Implement per-call timeout override\n- [ ] Use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header consistently\n- [ ] Implement HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all scenarios\n- [ ] Verify code coverage >= 80%\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/design.md","time":{"start":1775876397638,"end":1775876397649}}}}
